name: SPREAD COLORS
description: The "Lança perfume" is a chemical product used to clean toilets that gained fame in Rio de Janeiro carnivals in the early twentieth century. It was discovered its potential altering state of consciousness and quickly became fever in carnival events. In 1980 it was the theme of music for Rita Lee, and currently MC Jacaré. Today, forbidden, it is a drug used in "Baile Funk", stret carnival of Rio and parties throughout Brazil.
